  "explanation": "In determining the appropriate sentence, several factors were taken into consideration. Mitigating factors include the defendant's lack of a prior criminal record and the fact that partial restitution has already been made, showing remorse and a willingness to right the wrong. However, embezzling $25,000 constitutes a significant breach of trust between an employee and their employer. Furthermore, the spectator's outburst demanding a 10-year sentence is entirely disregarded, as sentencing must be based on law, precedent, and the specifics of the case, not emotional public opinion. Given the balance of the abuse of trust against the mitigating circumstances, a short period of incarceration coupled with probation and a mandate to complete restitution is appropriate.",
  "verdict": 6
}
